From 67238b4dd6ab6f799b329d354893a021789c2380 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Pablo=20Su=C3=A1rez=20Hern=C3=A1ndez?=
 <psuarezhernandez@suse.com>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 11:39:24 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Fix deprecation warnings when running on Python 3.13
 (Leap 16.0)

* Harden Python 3.12+ datetime and tar extraction usage

Route naive UTC time through salt.utils.timeutil (utcnow and utcfromtimestamp) across Salt modules, tests, and tooling instead of deprecated datetime constructors.

Add salt.utils.tarfileutil for tarfile extraction with PEP 706 filter=data on Python 3.12+, and use it from archive state, state.pkg, SPM local installs, and the salt-ssh shim. Keep bandit annotations where extraction remains inherently trusted.

Register warning filters for third-party datetime deprecation noise in salt.__init__. Extend unit tests for timeutil and tarfileutil.

* Migrate utcnow() leftovers to use salt.utils.timeutil

* `re.split`: replace 3rd arg with `maxsplit=`

`maxsplit` as positional argument is deprecated since Python 3.13.

---------

Co-authored-by: Daniel A. Wozniak <dan.woz@gmail.com>
Co-authored-by: Zaz Brown <zazbrown@zazbrown.com>
